  		<p><b>Description:</b></p>
  		
                <p>The Human vs. Zombies simulation was an assignment I made for my Interactive Media and Development class.</p>
                
                <p>The assignment is inspired by the tag/NERF game Humans vs. Zombies that is popular across college campuses across the United States. The simulation features zombies chasing humans through a wooded park with all participants avoiding trees in the progress. When a human is caught by a zombie it becomes a zombie as well.</p>
                
                <p>The game implements programming concepts such as autonomous agents and steering behavior (namely pursue,evade, obstacle avoid, and a modified stay in bounds behavior), collision detection, and enum-based state switching. The debug mode and options mode demonstrate a basic UI structure that helps the user understand and alter the simulation.</p>
  		
